T1  - Negative net foreign asset positions and stability in a world portfolio balance model
AU  - Henderson, Dale W.
AU  - Rogoff, Kenneth
JO  - Journal of International Economics
VL  - 13
IS  - 1
SP  - 85
EP  - 104
PY  - 1982
DA  - 1982/08/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(82)90007-1
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199682900071
AB  - Negative net foreign asset positions have been associated with a troublesome stability problem in flexible exchange rate regimes. In this paper a symmetrically-specified, two-country, portfolio balance model is employed to provide some perspective on this problem. It is concluded that negative net foreign asset positions do not constitute an independent source of instability. Instability can arise only under nonrational expectations or because of destabilizing speculation.
