UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/002219968290006X
AB  - Among those trade theorists who have studied the implications of variable returns to scale it has been almost standard practice to suppose that the variability of returns in each industry is generated by technical intra-industrial externalities. In the present paper inter-industrial as well as intra-industrial externalities are admitted. The topology of the set of production possibilities and of the locus of competitive outputs, as well as the robustness of several standard trade theorems, are examined.
ER  - 

